results.description:
After the success of Amazing Fantasy #15 (Aug. 1962) a few months later the same creative team came back to start an ongoing series focusing on the character the two of them created.

The series continued until #441 (Nov. 1998) when Marvel relaunched the title as Amazing Spider-Man Volume 2 with a new #1 in January 1999, but after issue #30 (#471) Marvel began to use a dual numbering system. And then on the 40th anniversary the numbering was returned again from issue #58 to #500 (Dec. 2003) as Amazing Spider-Man Volume 1.

This volume ends with #700 and is picked up by the Marvel Now! revolution volume Superior Spider-Man.
